    {
        "content": "<p>In what sense is it a congruence? I thought the proof would use induction</p>",
        "id": 534704667,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1755287307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well since <code>lhs = rhs</code></p>",
        "id": 534705049,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1755287517
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>then <code>∑ i, lhs i = ∑ i, rhs i</code> just by substituting</p>",
        "id": 534705101,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1755287544
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's simpler because you're summing over the whole type; <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Fintype.sum_congr#doc\">docs#Fintype.sum_congr</a> is slightly more involved because it only requires equality on the set you're summing over</p>",
        "id": 534708643,
